# Cursor Command File Format

When creating or editing files in `.cursor/commands/`, follow this format:

## File Structure

```markdown
# Command Title

Brief 1-2 sentence description of what this command does.

Steps:
- Step 1: Concise action
- Step 2: Concise action
- ...

[Optional] Match code style. Remind user to restart dev server.

Checklist: Item1, Item2, Item3
```

## Writing Guidelines

- Keep it short & sweet - agents work best with concise instructions
- Use imperative mood ("Create", "Verify", "Add")
- No code blocks - inline code with semicolons instead (e.g., `import { x } from "y"; export const z = x();`)
- Each step should be a single actionable item
- Include verification steps where needed
- End with a checklist summary

## Shareable Link Format

Generate links using: `https://cursor.com/link/command?name={name}&text={encoded_text}`

URL encoding rules:
- Spaces → `+`
- Newlines → `%0A`
- `#` → `%23`
- `@` → `%40`
- `/` → `%2F`
- `:` → `%3A`
- `;` → `%3B`
- `=` → `%3D`
- `{` → `%7B`
- `}` → `%7D`
- `"` → `%22`
- `,` → `%2C`
- Keep `(`, `)`, `-` as-is

Example link structure:
```
https://cursor.com/link/command?name=example&text=%23+Title%0A%0ADescription.%0A%0ASteps%3A%0A-+Step+one%0A-+Step+two
```
